15/09/2003
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- During a meeting Friday (12 September), Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and her Hungarian counterpart, Laszlo Kovacs, discussed the possible liberalisation of visa regimes. The two officials also discussed economic relations and agreed that their countries would soon sign an accord on co-operation in the areas of education, science and culture.
In other news Friday, the Macedonian Parliament adopted a law on the financing of political parties. The bill aims to establish control and transparency of party funding, with the goal of limiting corruption. (MIA - 12/09/03)
